<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFECFFCDA5CDF9171B63F824" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFECFFCDA5CDF9171C0CF929" blockId="28.[136,563,1741,1769]" box="[136,563,1741,1769]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading id="D0A781CFFFECFFCDA5CDF9171C0CF929" box="[136,563,1741,1769]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="4">
10. 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFECFFCDA5FCF9141C10F929" authority="Vahl (1804: 205)" authorityName="Vahl" authorityPageNumber="205" authorityYear="1804" box="[185,559,1741,1769]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFECFFCDA5FCF9141F58F928" bold="true" box="[185,359,1741,1768]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Stachytarpheta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFECFFCDA42BF9171C10F929" author="Vahl, M. H." box="[366,559,1742,1769]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref39740" refString="Vahl, M. H. (1804) Enumeratio plantarum vol. 1. N. Molleri &amp; Sons, Copenhagen, 381 pp." type="book" year="1804">Vahl (1804: 205)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFECFFCDA5CDF8CF1B63F824" blockId="28.[136,1452,1814,2093]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Herbs or shrubs, monoecious, branches without prickles, not aromatic. Leaves sessile or petiolate, glands near to the petiole absent. Inflorescences terminal, simple, racemes spiciform, multiflorous, rachis elongated; bracts membranaceous, green; bracteoles absent. Flowers sessile; calyx tubular, shorter than the corolla, immersed or not in the depressions of the rachis, membranaceous, green, 2‒4-toothed, persistent, accrescent in fruit; corolla zygomorphic, 5-lobed; stamens 2, staminodes 2, included, connective appendages absent, thecae divergent; ovary 1-carpelate, 2- loculate, ovules 1 per locle, stigma capitate. Fruit schizocarp, with 2 cluses, brown, external surface reticulate.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34A6528FFECFFCCA5F8F8371C9CFEE4" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BEF36A3FFECFFCCA5F8F8371C9CFEE4" blockId="28.[136,1452,1814,2093]" lastBlockId="29.[136,1451,158,293]" lastPageId="29" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFECFFCDA5F8F8371F58F7C8" authorityName="Vahl" authorityYear="1804" box="[189,359,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Stachytarpheta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFECFFCDA5F8F8371F58F7C8" box="[189,359,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Stachytarpheta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is part of the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D20FFECFFCDA777F8371D4CF7C8" authority="(Marx et al. 2010)" baseAuthorityName="Marx" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[562,883,2030,2056]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Duranteae">
Duranteae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFECFFCDA7F7F8371D54F7C8" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[690,875,2030,2056]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFECFFCDA7B3F8361D13F7C8" box="[758,812,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and presents approximately 120 species distributed throughout the Americas, Asia, Africa, and Oceania, with great diversity concentrated in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFECFFCDA121F7CB1A97F7EC" box="[1124,1192,2066,2092]" name="Brazil" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFECFFCDA1F3F7CB1B7BF7ED" author="Atkins, S." box="[1206,1348,2066,2093]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="161 - 272" refId="ref33024" refString="Atkins, S. (2005) The genus Stachytarpheta (Verbenaceae) in Brazil. Kew Bulletin 60: 161 - 272." type="journal article" year="2005">Atkins 2005</bibRefCitation>
, Cardoso 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEDFFCCA5CDFF461F1DFF78" box="[136,290,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al. in press.</emphasis>
). This is a monophyletic genus, characterized by the presence of the androecium with two fertile stamens and two staminodes (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEDFFCCA432FF1B1C05FF1C" author="Marx, H. &amp; O'Leary, N. &amp; Yuan, Y. &amp; Lu-Irving, P. &amp; Tank, D. &amp; Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R." box="[375,570,194,220]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1647 - 1663" refId="ref35509" refString="Marx, H., O'Leary, N., Yuan, Y., Lu-Irving, P., Tank, D., Mulgura, M. E. &amp; Olmstead, R. (2010) A molecular phylogeny and classification of Verbenaceae. American Journal of Botany 97: 1647 - 1663. https: // doi. org / 10.3732 / ajb. 1000144" type="journal article" year="2010">
Marx 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEDFFCCA4F8FF1A1FC9FF1C" box="[445,502,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). There are 82 species recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F3477633FFEDFFCCA687FF1B1A36FF1C" box="[962,1033,194,220]" name="Brazil" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, of which 75 are endemic, with most of the richness concentrated in 
<emphasis id="B924EAB1FFEDFFCCA4A4FF3F1C7FFEC0" box="[481,576,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Cerrado</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B52FFEDFFCCA70BFF3F1DB8FEC0" author="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G." box="[590,903,230,256]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref33512" refString="Cardoso, P. H. &amp; Salimena, F. R. G. (2020 c) Stachytarpheta in Flora do Brasil 2020 under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 15189 (accessed 4 January 2021)" type="url" year="2020">Cardoso &amp; Salimena 2020c</bibRefCitation>
). Seventeen species were recorded in the Atlantic Forest, of which six are found in 
<collectingRegion id="4994F841FFEDFFCCA4B9FED31CA1FEE4" box="[508,670,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
